SIMPLE: unaccustomed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unaccustomed
<hw>Un`ac*cus"tomed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Not used; not habituated; unfamiliar; unused; -- with
<ptcl>to</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Chastened as a bullock <qex>unaccustomed</qex> to the yoke.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. xxxi. 18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not usual; uncommon; strange; new.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What <qex>unaccustomed</qex> cause procures her hither?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unacquaintance</ent>⟦br⟧
